[Update a worklog entry|http://docs.atlassian.com/jira/REST/latest/#id245127] does not work using PUT method. 

h4. Steps to reproduce
1. Create a worklog using cURL using the command
{code}
curl -D- -u admin:admin -X POST --data @"C:/Users/chungpark/Desktop/data2.json" -H "Content-Type: application/json" http://localhost:8528/rest/api/2/issue/10100/worklog?
{code}
2. Use the PUT method to updateAuthor. And using the json data as shown in the JIRA REST API documentation.
{code}
{
	"self": "http://localhost:8528/rest/api/2/issue/10100/worklog/10101",
    "author": {
        "self": "http://localhost:8528/rest/api/2.0/user?username=admin",
        "name": "admin",
        "displayName": "admin",
        "active": false
    },
    "updateAuthor": {
        "self": "http://localhost:8528/rest/api/2.0/user?username=cp",
        "name": "cp",
        "displayName": "cp",
        "active": false
    },
	"comment": "-",
	"started": "2013-3-5T00:00:00.000+0000",
	"timeSpent": "30"
}
